## Routing

```
/splash                     SplashPage (sets sessionStorage hopahopa_splash_shown)
/welcome                    WelcomePage (slides → birthplace; slide Skip goes to birthplace; map only after birthplace Skip or save)
'' (root, splashGuard)
  map                       MapPage        (tab)
  stats                     StatsPage      (tab)
  settings                  SettingsPage   (tab)
  country/:code             CountryDetailPage
  ''                        → redirect to map
```

`splashGuard` is an inline guard in `app.routes.ts`; it redirects to `/splash` if `hopahopa_splash_shown` is not `'true'` in `sessionStorage`.

**Preloading:** `SelectivePreloadStrategy` (in `app.config.ts`) preloads only lazy routes marked with `data: { preload: true }` (the **map** tab). Stats, settings, and country detail load on first navigation.

> **Note:** First-run logic is handled entirely inside `SplashPage`. The `welcome.guard.ts` file has been deleted (it was dead code).

## Services

| Service | File | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| `CountryService` | `services/country.service.ts` | Source of truth for all ~195 countries; Angular **signals + computed** for counts; load/merge from storage; toggle visited; update stats/cities/notes; auto-save via `effect()`; on init and when birthplace is saved, **`syncBirthplaceIntoTravelData`** marks the birth country visited and adds the birth city (with coordinates) like a logged city |
| `StorageService` | `services/storage.service.ts` | **Capacitor Preferences** key `travelmap_countries`; generic JSON get/set/remove; migration from legacy localStorage; optional IndexedDB `HopaHopaDB` cleanup |
| `AchievementService` | `services/achievement.service.ts` | Milestone / continent / special achievements; sync unlock state with `CountryService`; celebrations (sound, haptics, modal); persists to `localStorage` key `hopahopa_achievements`; copy is **English** in code constants (`localizeAchievement` is a no-op pass-through) |
| `SettingsService` | `services/settings.service.ts` | Forces dark mode on `documentElement` / `body`; `resetSettings()` removes preferences key |
| `OverlayService` | `services/overlay.service.ts` | On `NavigationStart`, dismisses modals, popovers, alerts, action sheets; initialized from `AppComponent` |
| `PageTransitionService` | `services/page-transition.service.ts` | Shared state (position, country id/name) for map → country-detail transition animation |
| `ErrorService` | `services/error.service.ts` | User-facing toasts/alerts for categorized errors; logging helper |
| `CitySearchService` | `services/city-search.service.ts` | Wraps Mapbox Geocoding API (`/geocoding/v5/mapbox.places`) to return city suggestions filtered by country ISO code; used by `CountryDetailPage` and `WelcomePage` (birthplace city) |
| `BirthplaceService` | `services/birthplace.service.ts` | Load/save user birthplace for onboarding + map pin; persists via `StorageService` key `hopahopa_birthplace`; after save (and `CountryService` init), calls **`syncBirthplaceIntoTravelData`** so stats/achievements/map visited state match; `MapPage` still shows the dedicated birthplace layer + fly-to |
| `AssetPrefetchService` | `services/asset-prefetch.service.ts` | During **splash** and **welcome**, schedules (idle) dynamic `import()` of map / Mapbox / stats / settings chunks and `fetch` for `assets/countries.geojson` so cache is warm before the map opens |
| `CountryInsightsLoaderService` | `services/country-insights-loader.service.ts` | One-time `HttpClient` load of `assets/data/country-insights.json` (see **`build:insights-from-travel`**); per-code `CountryInsightsBundle` + optional **`wikipediaAttribution`**; regional fallbacks from `country-insights.data.ts` |
| `MapInstanceBridgeService` | `services/map-instance-bridge.service.ts` | Holds the live Mapbox `Map` from `MapPage` so `TravelReelComponent` can sample the real globe; cleared when the map page is destroyed |

## Shared components

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `AnimatedBackgroundComponent` | Decorative background used on several pages |
| `AchievementModalComponent` | Celebration modal (lazy-imported by `AchievementService`) |
| `CircularMenuComponent` | Long-press radial menu on the map |
| `CountryPreviewCardComponent` | Hover/tap preview card on map |
| `TravelReelComponent` | Full-screen ~21 s canvas animation (intro globe → stats → countries → achievements → outro) recorded via `MediaRecorder` (prefers **MP4/H.264** when the browser supports it; otherwise **WebM**) and shared via the system sheet; **Settings** “Record travel reel” navigates to **`/map?travelReel=1`**, **`MapPage`** lazy-mounts the reel so the intro samples the live map canvas; enabled once **at least one country** is visited; **dynamic-imported**; if no map canvas, procedural fallback |

**Directive:** `ButtonPressDirective` (`appButtonPress`) — press animation + Capacitor haptics.

## Domain models (`src/app/models/country.model.ts`)

```typescript
interface Country {
  code: string;       // ISO alpha-2
  name: string;
  visited: boolean;
  photoIds: string[];
  visitCount?: number;
  daysStayed?: number;
  cities?: string[];
  cityCoordinates?: Record<string, [number, number]>; // city name → [lng, lat] for map pins
  note?: string;      // max 120 chars enforced in CountryService
}
```

Other types: `Birthplace`, `BIRTHPLACE_STORAGE_KEY`, `isValidBirthplace()` (`models/birthplace.model.ts`); `Achievement`, `UnlockedAchievement`, `AchievementCategory` (in `AchievementService`); `TransitionState` (in `PageTransitionService`); `AppSettings` (in `SettingsService`); `ErrorContext` / `ErrorType` (in `ErrorService`).

## Storage keys

| Key | Storage | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `travelmap_countries` | Capacitor Preferences | Serialized country array |
| `hopahopa_birthplace` | Capacitor Preferences | JSON `Birthplace` (country + city + coordinates); cleared on full data reset |
| `hopahopa_achievements` | `localStorage` | Unlocked achievement IDs |
| `hopahopa_welcome_seen` | `localStorage` | `'true'` after onboarding |
| `hopahopa_splash_shown` | `sessionStorage` | `'true'` per session |

## External APIs

- **Mapbox:** map tiles + dark style (`mapbox://styles/mapbox/dark-v11`); token from `environment.mapboxToken`
- **GeoJSON (countries):** `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datasets/geo-countries/master/data/countries.geojson` with fallback to `assets/countries.geojson`
- **Country detail blurbs:** `assets/data/country-insights.json` is keyed by ISO alpha-2 and consumed by `CountryInsightsLoaderService`. Regenerate from **`src/assets/travel.json`** with **`npm run build:insights-from-travel`** (maps `mustKnow` / `mustDo` / `myths` / `adventureHighlights` → `atAGlance` / `whyVisit` / `tasteAndTraditions` / `planSmart`). Optional legacy pipeline: **`npm run generate:insights`** (Wikipedia-derived) if that script is still used in your workflow.
- **No custom REST backend** — fully offline-first; all data lives on-device

## Capacitor plugins in use

`@capacitor/app`, `@capacitor/camera`, `@capacitor/filesystem`, `@capacitor/haptics`, `@capacitor/keyboard`, `@capacitor/preferences`, `@capacitor/share`, `@capacitor/splash-screen`, `@capacitor/status-bar`

**Android / iOS:** `TravelReelComponent` writes the file to **External** app storage when possible, else **Cache**, then shares via `@capacitor/share` (`url` first, then `files`). `android/app/src/main/res/xml/file_paths.xml` exposes **cache**, **files**, and **external-files** for `FileProvider`. Instagram often expects **MP4**; many in-app browsers only produce **WebM**, so the UI explains using **Save to Photos/Files** then uploading from the target app.

## Known caveats / tech debt

- **GitHub Pages vs local:** `ng serve` uses `<base href="/">`; CI (`.github/workflows/build.yml`) builds with `--base-href=/<repository-name>/` so asset and lazy chunk URLs match `https://<user>.github.io/<repo>/`. If you deploy manually, use the same `--base-href` or the app will load wrong. **Mapbox:** production token is injected in CI via `MAPBOX_TOKEN`; if the Mapbox token has **URL restrictions** that only list `localhost`, map tiles fail on GitHub Pages while local dev works—add `https://*.github.io/*` (or your exact Pages URL) in the Mapbox dashboard
- Adding or renaming countries in `countries.data.ts`: update **`src/assets/travel.json`** (if used), run **`npm run build:insights-from-travel`**, and commit **`assets/data/country-insights.json`** so country detail blurbs stay in sync
- `zone.js` remains a devDependency for Karma (`src/test.ts`); the app runtime is zoneless (`provideZonelessChangeDetection`)
- `StorageService.loadCountries()` currently maps only `code`, `name`, `visited`, `photoIds` — `visitCount`, `daysStayed`, `cities`, `note` may not survive a full reload
- `src/environments/environment.ts` is gitignored (developer local copy); copy from `environment.example.ts` and fill in your Mapbox token for local dev
- The pre-existing `Cannot find module '../../environments/environment'` lint error in `map.page.ts` is expected in CI/readonly environments where `environment.ts` is absent
- **UI language:** The app is **English-only** (no runtime translation layer or locale JSON)
